| ğŸ” **Security**       | Protects against DDoS attacks, adds HTTPS, and hides origin IP |
| ğŸ“ˆ **Scalability**    | Handles traffic spikes without overloading origin servers |
| ğŸ›¡ï¸ **Reliability**    | Provides failover and redundancy in case of server outages |

---

## ğŸ§  How It Works

1. You upload your content (e.g., images, JS files) to your origin server.
2. The CDN caches this content across its global edge servers.
3. When a user requests a file, the CDN serves it from the **nearest edge node**, not your origin.

